cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper is about automating the design of neural network architectures, which is a topic that falls under the sub-fields of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper specifically focuses on creating a search space for neural architectures using a corpus of existing architectures, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning and computer vision research. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG and cs.CV, followed by cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.IR.
